Reasoning: The paper discusses measuring scientific efficiency and citation impact, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with measuring the impact of research publications. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant as it deals with measuring the relevance and impact of information. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as it deals with measuring the impact of research in social networks. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as it deals with the social and ethical implications of research. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still relevant as it deals with measuring the impact of research in security and privacy.
